# Frontend Environment Variables

## Required Variables

### API Configuration
VITE_API_URL=https://your-backend-url.com/api/v1

### Stripe Payment Processing
VITE_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_your_stripe_publishable_key

### Firebase Configuration
VITE_API_KEY=your_firebase_api_key
VITE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your-project.firebaseapp.com
VITE_PROJECT_ID=your-firebase-project-id
VITE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your-project.appspot.com
VITE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=your_messaging_sender_id
VITE_APP_ID=your_firebase_app_id
VITE_MEASUREMENT_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX

## Notes

- Never commit your .env file to version control
- Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values
- For production, set these variables in your hosting platform's environment configuration
- All variables prefixed with VITE_ are exposed to the client-side code
- Do not put sensitive secrets in frontend environment variables
